No. —,

Original.

Ex parte: In the Matter of The Seneca Nation et al., Petitioners. Submitted October 9, 1906. Decided October 15, 1906. Mr. Chester Howe for petitioners. Mr. W. H. Robeson, Mr. J. J. Hemp-hill, Mr. A. B. Browne and Mr. Alexander Britton for respondents. Mr. Assistant Attorney General Van Orsdel for the United States. Per Curiam.

Motion for leave to file petition for a writ of mandamus denied.
